@div segment A

1. iri mu-bi-gin₇ me-a tum₂-ma
#lem: iri[city]; mu[name]; me[Being]; tum[suitable]
#etcsl: line-id=A.1

#note: Cited in OB catalogue in the Louvre, 0.2.02, line 62

2. eš₃ urim₂{ki} ud huš ki-en-gi-ra me₃ ki us₂-sa
#lem: eš[shrine]; Urim[1]SN; ud[storm]; huš[reddish]; Kengir[1]; me[battle]; ki[place]; us[accompany]
#etcsl: line-id=A.2

3. numun i-i suhuš kalam-ma gen₆-ne₂ he₂-ŋal₂ ki us₂-sa
#lem: numun[seed]; e[bring out]; suhuš[foundation]; kalam[the Land (of Sumer)]; gin[confirm]; heŋal[plenty]; ki[place]; us[accompany]
#etcsl: line-id=A.3

4. barag mah an-na ki kug ki sikil
#lem: barag[sanctum]; mah[great]; An[1]DN; ki[place]; kug[purify]; ki[place]; sikil[purify]
#etcsl: line-id=A.4

5. niŋ₂-saŋ gu₇ an-ne₂ ni₂ te-en-ten lal₃ ŋeštin biz-biz-ze₂-da ki us₂-sa
#lem: nesaŋ[first-fruit offering]; gu[eat]; An[1]DN; ni[self]; ten[extinguish]; lal[syrup]; ŋeštin[vine]; biz[trickle]; ki[place]; us[accompany]
#etcsl: line-id=A.5

6. du₆-ur₂ ki mu tuku {d}en-lil₂-la₂ šag₄-bi me hal-ha
#lem: Duʾur[1]TN; ki[place]; mu[name]; tuku[acquire]; Enlil[1]DN; šag[heart]; me[Being]; hal[divide]
#etcsl: line-id=A.6

7. ki nam tar-ra a-a {d}en-lil₂-la₂ barag gal ki us₂-sa
#lem: ki[place]; nam[fate]; tar[cut]; aya[father]; Enlil[1]DN; barag[sanctum]; gal[big]; ki[place]; us[accompany]
#etcsl: line-id=A.7

8. eridug{ki} eš₃ kug-zu nam tar-ra me nun me sikil-la ki us₂-sa
#lem: Eridug[1]SN; eš[shrine]; kugzu[wise]; nam[fate]; tar[cut]; me[Being]; nun[prince]; me[Being]; sikil[pure]; ki[place]; us[accompany]
#etcsl: line-id=A.8

9. e₂-kiš-nu-ŋal₂-la tur₃ {d}suen-na
#lem: Ekišnuŋal[1]TN; tur[animal stall]; Suen[1]DN
#etcsl: line-id=A.9

